   "source": [
    "# Quantum Machine Learning: Banknote Authentication\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates a Qiskit-based quantum classifier for banknote authentication classification using extracted pixels from an image.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Dataset:** 1,371 samples, 4 features (variance, skewness, curtosis, entropy of Wavelet-transformed banknote images), binary label (0 = authentic, 1 = forged).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pipeline:**\n",
    "1. Load & explore the dataset\n",
    "2. Split & normalize\n",
    "3. Classical SVM baseline (RBF kernel)\n",
    "4. Quantum Kernel Classifier (ZZ Feature Map, 4 qubits)\n",
    "5. Results comparison & visualization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3e43f332",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1: Import the required libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "b5125a00",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "All libraries imported successfully!\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "#import sys\n",
    "#print(sys.executable)\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.svm import SVC\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import (\n",
    "    accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score,\n",
    "    f1_score, confusion_matrix\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Qiskit imports\n",
    "from qiskit import QuantumCircuit\n",
    "from qiskit.circuit import ParameterVector\n",
    "from qiskit_machine_learning.kernels import FidelityQuantumKernel\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"All libraries imported successfully!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "94211762",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Step 2: Load and Prepare the Banknote Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "Features (extracted from Wavelet-transformed images):\n",
    "- **Variance** – spread of pixel intensities\n",
    "- **Skewness** – asymmetry of the pixel distribution\n",
    "- **Curtosis** – peakedness of the pixel distribution\n",
    "- **Entropy** – measure of randomness\n",
    "\n",
    "Label: **0** = authentic, **1** = forged"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "8a5252b3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
